{\an1}( <i>horn honking )</i>

01:03.330 --> 01:04.340
{\an1}D-OHH!

01:04.390 --> 01:05.190
{\an1}( <i>screams )</i>

01:37.390 --> 01:38.490
{\an1}♪ You can Mash... ♪

01:38.560 --> 01:40.400
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hMarty:
Doing the Monster Mash with you

01:40.460 --> 01:42.730
{\an1}on this beautiful
Valentine's Day.

01:42.800 --> 01:45.600
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hBill:
Marty, why did you play
that song today?

01:45.670 --> 01:48.540
{\an1}There must be thousands
\h\h\h\hof love songs.

01:48.600 --> 01:50.770
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hMarty:
It's kind of a love song.

01:50.840 --> 01:53.040
{\an1}\h\h\h\hThe monsters enjoying
each other's company, dancing.

01:53.110 --> 01:54.480
{\an1}Holding their evil in check.

01:54.540 --> 01:56.240
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hBill:
You played the wrong record,
didn't you?

01:56.310 --> 01:58.680
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hMarty:
Why are you doing this to me?

02:02.050 --> 02:04.750
{\an1}BAH! THIS IS JUST ANOTHER
HALLMARK HOLIDAY

02:04.820 --> 02:06.920
{\an1}COOKED UP TO SELL CARDS.

02:06.990 --> 02:10.729
{\an1}OH, A VALENTINE
FROM MY GRANDDAUGHTER.

02:10.789 --> 02:13.230
{\an1}COULD I HAVE THE ENVELOPE?

02:13.300 --> 02:17.180
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h"TO MOE,
FROM YOUR SECRET ADMIRER."

02:17.230 --> 02:18.830
{\an1}YOO-HOO!

02:18.900 --> 02:20.670
{\an1}OH, GOD, NO!

02:20.740 --> 02:22.170
{\an1}( <i>belching )</i>

02:22.240 --> 02:25.010
{\an1}AND THIS IS
FOR MY HUGGY BUG

02:25.070 --> 02:27.280
{\an1}IN HONOR
OF THIS SPECIAL DAY.

02:27.340 --> 02:28.610
{\an1}<i>SPECIAL DAY?</i>

02:28.680 --> 02:30.550
{\an1}<i>WHAT HAVE I FORGOTTEN NOW?</i>

02:30.610 --> 02:31.950
{\an1}<i>NOW DON'T PANIC.</i>

02:32.010 --> 02:33.010
{\an1}<i>IS IT BACON DAY?</i>

02:33.080 --> 02:34.050
{\an1}<i>NO, THAT'S CRAZY TALK.</i>

02:34.120 --> 02:35.680
{\an1}<i>SHE'S GETTING IMPATIENT.</i>

02:35.750 --> 02:36.950
{\an1}<i>TAKE A STAB AT IT.</i>

02:37.020 --> 02:39.890
{\an1}HAPPY VALENTINE'S DAY.

02:39.960 --> 02:41.500
{\an1}OH, THANK YOU, DEAR.

02:41.560 --> 02:43.220
{\an1}WOO-HOO!

02:43.290 --> 02:45.630
{\an1}I'LL BET YOU HAVE
A LOT OF THINGS PLANNED,
HEY DAD?

02:45.690 --> 02:47.430
{\an1}UH, KIND OF.

02:47.500 --> 02:51.670
{\an1}NOBODY MAKES A BIG DEAL
OUT OF VALENTINE'S DAY.

02:51.730 --> 02:54.170
{\an1}♪ IF YOU THINK I'M CUDDLY ♪

02:54.240 --> 02:56.770
{\an1}♪ AND YOU WANT MY COMPANY ♪

02:56.840 --> 02:59.810
{\an1}♪ COME ON, WIFEY, LET ME KNOW ♪

02:59.880 --> 03:02.550
{\an1}♪ OW, OW, OWW! ♪

03:02.610 --> 03:05.210
{\an1}HEY, DAD, WHY DON'T YOU
GIVE MOM HER PRESENT.

03:05.280 --> 03:07.950
{\an1}WHAT A NICE IDEA, SON.

03:08.020 --> 03:10.250
{\an1}IT'S, UH...

03:10.320 --> 03:13.120
{\an1}UPSTAIRS ON THE SECOND FLOOR
\h\h\h\hOF OUR HOUSE.

03:13.190 --> 03:15.690
{\an1}I'LL JUST GO GET IT.

03:15.760 --> 03:19.660
{\an1}( <i>footsteps )</i>

03:19.730 --> 03:21.460
{\an1}( <i>Homer grunting and groaning)</i>

03:21.530 --> 03:23.300
{\an1}( <i>screaming )</i>

03:24.530 --> 03:26.200
{\an1}APU, YOU GOT
TO HELP ME.

03:26.270 --> 03:29.270
{\an1}I NEED A VALENTINE'S GIFT
\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hFOR MY WIFE.

03:29.340 --> 03:31.410
{\an1}PERHAPS THIS MIGHT
BE APPROPRIATE.

03:31.470 --> 03:33.070
{\an1}YES! YOU SAVED MY LIFE.

03:33.140 --> 03:34.410
{\an1}HOW MUCH?

03:34.480 --> 03:35.610
{\an1}$100.

03:35.680 --> 03:36.980
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hWHAT?
THAT'S HIGHWAY ROBBERY.

03:37.050 --> 03:38.180
{\an1}I WON'T PAY IT.

03:38.250 --> 03:39.750
{\an1}OH, I THINK YOU WILL.

03:39.820 --> 03:41.860
{\an1}FORGET IT, PAL.

03:41.920 --> 03:47.190
{\an1}( <i>humming )</i>

03:47.260 --> 03:50.160
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hALL RIGHT!
BUT I'LL NEVER SHOP HERE AGAIN.

03:50.230 --> 03:52.930
{\an1}<i>IF HE DISCOVERS THE DISCOUNT
\h\h\hSUPERMARKET NEXT DOOR</i>

03:52.990 --> 03:54.360
{\an1}<i>ALL IS LOST.</i>

03:54.430 --> 03:56.260
{\an1}NICKEL OFF ON EXPIRED BABY FOOD.

03:56.330 --> 03:57.600
{\an1}SOLD!

03:57.670 --> 04:00.340
{\an1}\h\h\hMISS HOOVER, CAN WE
EXCHANGE OUR VALENTINES?

04:00.400 --> 04:01.840
{\an1}NOT JUST YET, JANEY.

04:01.900 --> 04:04.370
{\an1}\h\hFIRST, WE'RE GOING TO
CONSTRUCT PAPER MAILBOXES

04:04.440 --> 04:05.970
{\an1}TO STORE THE VALENTINES.

04:06.040 --> 04:07.980
{\an1}ISN'T THAT POINTLESS BUSYWORK?

04:08.040 --> 04:09.410
{\an1}BULL'S-EYE! GET CRACKING.

04:09.480 --> 04:11.710
{\an1}YES, RALPH?

04:11.780 --> 04:13.950
{\an1}MY PARENTS WON'T LET ME
\h\h\h\h\hUSE SCISSORS.

04:14.020 --> 04:15.350
{\an1}( <i>children giggling )</i>

04:15.420 --> 04:18.390
{\an1}THE CHILDREN ARE RIGHT
\h\h\hTO LAUGH AT YOU.

04:18.450 --> 04:19.850
{\an1}\h\h\h\hTHESE THINGS
COULDN'T CUT BUTTER.

04:19.920 --> 04:22.060
{\an1}NOW TAKE OUT YOUR RED CRAYONS.

04:22.120 --> 04:23.220
{\an1}MISS HOOVER?

04:23.290 --> 04:24.390
{\an1}YES, RALPH?

04:24.460 --> 04:26.660
{\an1}I DON'T HAVE A RED CRAYON.

04:26.730 --> 04:27.460
{\an1}WHY NOT?

04:27.530 --> 04:29.430
{\an1}I ATE IT.

04:30.800 --> 04:32.230
{\an1}Attention, everyone.

04:32.300 --> 04:33.840
{\an1}This is Principal Skinner.

04:33.900 --> 04:36.340
{\an1}\h\h\h\hSOME STUDENT,
POSSIBLY BART SIMPSON

04:36.400 --> 04:38.410
{\an1}HAS BEEN CIRCULATING
\h\h\h\hCANDY HEARTS

04:38.470 --> 04:41.080
{\an1}FEATURING CRUDE, OFF-COLOR
\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hSENTIMENTS.

04:41.140 --> 04:42.440
{\an1}LET ME TELL YOU SOMETHING.

04:42.510 --> 04:44.410
{\an1}VALENTINE'S DAY IS NO JOKE.

04:52.720 --> 04:54.720
{\an1}SENDING YOUR CHICK
\hA VALENTINE, HUH?

04:54.790 --> 04:56.790
{\an1}YEP.

04:56.860 --> 04:59.190
{\an1}( <i>gunfire and screaming )</i>

04:59.260 --> 05:01.200
{\an1}JOHNNY.

05:01.260 --> 05:02.530
{\an1}JOHNNY!

05:02.600 --> 05:04.900
{\an1}Johnny-y-y-y!!

05:04.970 --> 05:06.370
{\an1}COOL.

05:06.430 --> 05:07.870
{\an1}I BROKE HIS BRAIN.

05:07.940 --> 05:09.070
{\an1}ALL RIGHT, CHILDREN.

05:09.140 --> 05:12.170
{\an1}YOU MAY NOW EXCHANGE VALENTINES.

05:12.240 --> 05:15.810
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hMISS HOOVER,
I GLUED MY HEAD TO MY SHOULDER.

05:15.880 --> 05:16.640
{\an1}( <i>chuckling )</i>

05:27.390 --> 05:29.490
{\an1}( <i>sniffling )</i>

05:29.560 --> 05:31.430
{\an1}( <i>sobbing )</i>

05:31.490 --> 05:33.130
{\an1}POOR RALPH.

05:34.600 --> 05:36.500
{\an1}HERE YOU GO, RALPH.

05:36.570 --> 05:37.180
{\an1}( <i>gasps )</i>

05:38.770 --> 05:41.440
{\an1}YOU CHOO-CHOO-CHOOSE ME?

05:41.500 --> 05:43.470
{\an1}HAPPY VALENTINE'S.

05:45.840 --> 05:47.740
{\an1}( <i>sighing )</i>

05:49.880 --> 05:51.780
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\hALL RIGHT,
SPECIAL HOLIDAY MEAL.

05:54.720 --> 05:56.720
{\an1}\hWHERE DO YOU WANT
THESE BEEF HEARTS?

05:56.790 --> 05:57.730
{\an1}ON THE FLOOR.

05:57.790 --> 05:58.990
{\an1}IT DOESN'T LOOK VERY CLEAN.

05:59.050 --> 06:00.920
{\an1}JUST DO YOUR JOB, HEART-BOY.

06:02.860 --> 06:04.860
{\an1}( <i>creaking )</i>

06:11.330 --> 06:13.900
{\an1}( <i>moaning )</i>

06:13.970 --> 06:16.000
{\an1}BART, WHAT'S WRONG?

06:16.070 --> 06:17.410
{\an1}MY BABOON HEART.

06:17.470 --> 06:18.910
{\an1}BODY...

06:18.970 --> 06:20.310
{\an1}REJECTING IT.

06:21.510 --> 06:23.340
{\an1}( <i>screaming )</i>

06:23.410 --> 06:24.380
{\an1}MM-HMM.

06:29.950 --> 06:33.790
{\an1}CAN I WALK YOU HOME...
\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hVALENTINE?

06:33.860 --> 06:35.460
{\an1}SURE, I GUESS.

06:35.520 --> 06:38.730
{\an1}THAT VALENTINE
SURE WAS FUNNY.

06:38.790 --> 06:40.800
{\an1}GLAD YOU LIKED IT.

06:40.860 --> 06:44.530
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\h\hIT SAYS,
"CHOO-CHOO-CHOOSE ME."

06:44.600 --> 06:47.370
{\an1}AND THERE'S A PICTURE
\h\h\h\h\hOF A TRAIN.

06:47.440 --> 06:49.370
{\an1}YEAH, NICE GAG.

06:49.440 --> 06:52.310
{\an1}AH, SO...

06:52.370 --> 06:57.040
{\an1}DO YOU LIKE... STUFF?

06:58.980 --> 07:02.480
{\an1}THE DOCTOR SAID I WOULDN'T
\h\hHAVE SO MANY NOSEBLEEDS

07:02.550 --> 07:05.120
{\an1}IF I KEPT MY FINGER
\h\h\hOUT OF THERE.

07:05.190 --> 07:07.260
{\an1}WELL, HERE'S MY HOUSE.

07:11.230 --> 07:13.230
{\an1}♪ <i>The Itchy & Scratchy Show ♪</i>

07:42.860 --> 07:46.790
{\an1}Hey, kids, don't forget to watch
\h\h\hmy 29th Anniversary Show

07:46.860 --> 07:50.160
{\an1}featuring clips like this one
\h\h\h\h\h\h\hof Sideshow Mel

07:50.230 --> 07:52.300
{\an1}whacked out on wowee sauce.

07:52.370 --> 07:55.140
{\an1}\h( <i>drunkenly: )
Everyone's always
kissing your ass.</i>

07:55.200 --> 07:58.110
{\an1}Well, I'm not afraid
\h\h\h\h\hto tell you

07:58.170 --> 08:00.480
{\an1}you're a ( <i>bleep ).</i>

08:00.540 --> 08:03.680
{\an1}\h\hI'D GIVE ANYTHING
TO GO TO THAT SHOW.

08:03.750 --> 08:05.720
{\an1}I'D SELL MY FIRST-BORN SON.

08:05.780 --> 08:06.650
{\an1}HEY!

08:06.720 --> 08:08.130
{\an1}YOU'LL DO AS YOU'RE TOLD.

08:08.180 --> 08:09.580
{\an1}RALPH THINKS
\h\hI LIKE HIM

08:09.650 --> 08:11.190
{\an1}BUT I ONLY GAVE HIM
\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hA VALENTINE

08:11.250 --> 08:13.050
{\an1}\h'CAUSE I FELT
SORRY FOR HIM.

08:13.120 --> 08:14.460
{\an1}AH, SWEET PITY.

08:14.520 --> 08:16.990
{\an1}WHERE WOULD MY LOVE LIFE
\h\hHAVE BEEN WITHOUT IT?

08:17.060 --> 08:18.090
{\an1}WHAT DO YOU SAY
\h\h\h\h\h\h\hTO A BOY

08:18.160 --> 08:19.730
{\an1}\h\h\h\hTO LET HIM KNOW
YOU'RE NOT INTERESTED?

08:19.790 --> 08:21.160
{\an1}WELL, HONEY...

08:21.230 --> 08:23.400
{\an1}LET ME HANDLE THIS, MARGE.
\h\h\hI'VE HEARD THEM ALL.

08:23.470 --> 08:25.180
{\an1}"I LIKE YOU AS A FRIEND."

08:25.230 --> 08:26.930
{\an1}I THINK WE SHOULD
SEE OTHER PEOPLE.

08:27.000 --> 08:28.400
{\an1}"I NO SPEAK ENGLISH."

08:28.470 --> 08:29.570
{\an1}I GET THE IDEA.

08:29.640 --> 08:30.910
{\an1}"I'M MARRIED TO THE SEA."

08:30.970 --> 08:32.070
{\an1}I DON'T WANT TO KILL YOU,
\h\h\h\h\h\h\hBUT I WILL.

08:32.140 --> 08:33.470
{\an1}HONEY!

08:33.539 --> 08:36.039
{\an1}I'D TELL THIS BOY THAT
YOU'RE VERY FLATTERED

08:36.110 --> 08:39.010
{\an1}BUT YOU'RE NOT READY
FOR THIS KIND OF THING.

08:39.080 --> 08:40.080
{\an1}THANKS, MOM.

08:40.150 --> 08:41.549
{\an1}IF THAT DOESN'T WORK

08:41.620 --> 08:42.850
{\an1}SIX SIMPLE WORDS:

08:42.919 --> 08:45.290
{\an1}\h\h"I'M NOT GAY,
BUT I'LL LEARN."

08:45.350 --> 08:48.460
{\an1}RALPH, I THINK YOU'RE NICE,
\h\h\h\h\hBUT I'M NOT READY

08:48.520 --> 08:49.790
{\an1}FOR THIS KIND OF THING.

08:49.860 --> 08:50.960
{\an1}DO YOU UNDERSTAND?

08:51.030 --> 08:52.290
{\an1}I GUESS SO.

08:52.360 --> 08:53.530
{\an1}GOOD.

08:56.830 --> 09:00.100
{\an1}DAD, HOW DO YOU GET
A GIRL TO LIKE YOU?

09:00.170 --> 09:03.440
{\an1}SON, WHETHER YOU WANT TO WIN
A GIRL OR CRACK A NUT

09:03.510 --> 09:05.450
{\an1}THE KEY IS PERSISTENCE.

09:05.510 --> 09:09.510
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\h\h\hKEEP AT IT,
AND NEVER LOSE YOUR COOL.

09:09.580 --> 09:12.080
{\an1}AH, COME ON,
YOU STUPID...

09:12.150 --> 09:13.550
{\an1}( <i>gunshot )</i>

09:13.620 --> 09:17.160
{\an1}\h\h\hLET THAT BE A LESSON
TO THE REST OF YOU... NUTS.

09:17.220 --> 09:18.320
{\an1}OKAY, DAD.

09:18.390 --> 09:19.650
{\an1}I'LL BE PERSISTENT.

09:19.720 --> 09:21.290
{\an1}IS THAT HOW YOU GOT MOM?

09:21.360 --> 09:23.060
{\an1}WELL, SON

09:23.120 --> 09:26.290
{\an1}NEVER UNDERESTIMATE THE APPEAL
\h\h\h\h\hOF A MAN IN UNIFORM.

09:26.360 --> 09:27.730
{\an1}OH, YEAH!

09:31.770 --> 09:33.940
{\an1}Hey, boys and girls,
\h\h\honly four days

09:34.000 --> 09:35.640
{\an1}till my anniversary show.

09:35.700 --> 09:38.210
{\an1}29 years-- and when I came on

09:38.270 --> 09:40.540
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\h\h\hthey said
I wouldn't last a week.

09:40.610 --> 09:42.810
{\an1}\h\h\hYou know where
those reviewers are?

09:42.880 --> 09:44.150
{\an1}All dead.

09:44.210 --> 09:46.780
{\an1}How you doing down there,
\h\h\h\hfellas? Huh? Huh?

09:46.850 --> 09:48.350
{\an1}Anyway, here's a clip.

09:48.420 --> 09:53.250
{\an1}Now why do they call this
\h\h\h\h\ha urine monkey?

09:53.320 --> 09:56.290
{\an1}Oh... I just found out.

09:56.360 --> 09:58.960
{\an1}\h\h\h\hTHAT'S FUNNY
FOR SO MANY REASONS.

09:59.030 --> 10:00.530
{\an1}WE HAVE TO GO
TO THAT SHOW.

10:00.600 --> 10:01.630
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hFORGET IT.
TO GET THOSE TICKETS

10:01.700 --> 10:03.900
{\an1}OUR PARENTS WOULD
\h\hHAVE TO BE PART

10:03.970 --> 10:05.470
{\an1}OF SPRINGFIELD'S
\hCULTURAL ELITE.

10:05.530 --> 10:07.440
{\an1}CAN YOU BELIEVE FLANDERS

10:07.500 --> 10:09.640
{\an1}THREW OUT A PERFECTLY
\h\hGOOD TOOTHBRUSH?

10:11.870 --> 10:13.410
{\an1}EW.

10:13.480 --> 10:14.650
{\an1}( <i>doorbell ringing )</i>

10:16.410 --> 10:18.350
{\an1}OH, NO, IT'S RALPH.

10:18.410 --> 10:20.880
{\an1}JUST MAKE UP SOME EXCUSE.

10:20.950 --> 10:22.750
{\an1}SHE'S IN THE CAN.
\h\h\h\hGO AWAY.

10:22.820 --> 10:23.820
{\an1}YES, SIR.

10:23.890 --> 10:25.430
{\an1}I'D DO ANYTHING FOR LISA.

10:25.490 --> 10:28.060
{\an1}REALLY?

10:30.460 --> 10:34.500
{\an1}MR. SIMPSON, THE TAR FUMES
\h\h\hARE MAKING ME DIZZY.

10:34.560 --> 10:37.060
{\an1}YEAH, THEY'LL DO THAT.

10:38.870 --> 10:40.530
{\an1}DEAREST MARTHA, SINCE BOYHOOD

10:40.600 --> 10:43.870
{\an1}\hI HAVE YEARNED TO BE
ON THE ONE-DOLLAR BILL

10:43.940 --> 10:47.140
{\an1}\h\hAND WITH YOUR HELP,
THIS, I SHALL ACHIEVE.

10:47.210 --> 10:49.380
{\an1}SINCERELY, GEORGE WASHINGTON.

10:49.440 --> 10:50.680
{\an1}( <i>class applauds )</i>

10:50.750 --> 10:51.580
{\an1}THANK YOU, REX.

10:54.080 --> 10:56.980
{\an1}\h\h\h\hI'VE SELECTED THE CAST
FOR OUR PRESIDENTS' DAY PAGEANT.

10:57.050 --> 10:59.120
{\an1}\h\hMARTHA WASHINGTON
WILL BE PLAYED BY...

10:59.190 --> 11:00.920
{\an1}LISA SIMPSON.

11:00.990 --> 11:03.560
{\an1}\h\hGEORGE WASHINGTON
WILL BE PLAYED BY...

11:03.630 --> 11:04.840
{\an1}( <i>clears throat )</i>

11:04.890 --> 11:06.130
{\an1}RALPH WIGGUM.

11:06.190 --> 11:07.190
{\an1}HMM...

11:07.260 --> 11:09.600
{\an1}WHAT? THIS IS A TRAVESTY.

11:09.660 --> 11:11.500
{\an1}\h\hEVERYONE KNOWS
I'M THE BEST ACTOR

11:11.570 --> 11:12.870
{\an1}IN THIS RIDICULOUS SCHOOL.

11:12.930 --> 11:13.930
{\an1}SIT DOWN, REX.

11:14.000 --> 11:15.370
{\an1}I WILL NOT SIT DOWN.

11:15.440 --> 11:17.840
{\an1}SOMEONE'S GOTTEN TO YOU,
\h\h\hYOU DECEITFUL COW.

11:17.910 --> 11:19.070
{\an1}THAT'S ABSURD, REX.

11:19.140 --> 11:21.710
{\an1}RALPH WON THE PART
\hFAIR AND SQUARE.

11:21.780 --> 11:23.410
{\an1}THAT'S THE SIGNAL.

11:23.480 --> 11:26.250
{\an1}\h\h\hTAKE THE BOOT
OFF THE CAR, BOYS.

11:27.920 --> 11:29.680
{\an1}RALPH IS IN THE PLAY
\h\h\h\h\h\hWITH ME.

11:29.750 --> 11:31.890
{\an1}I KNOW HE'S GOING
\hTO EMBARRASS ME

11:31.950 --> 11:33.850
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\h\hIN FRONT
OF THE WHOLE SCHOOL.

11:33.920 --> 11:34.790
{\an1}( <i>knocking )</i>

11:34.860 --> 11:35.920
{\an1}HUH?

11:37.930 --> 11:41.100
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hOH, NO,
IT'S A PACKAGE FROM RALPH.

11:42.830 --> 11:46.600
{\an1}OH, A MALIBU STACY CONVERTIBLE.

11:46.670 --> 11:48.300
{\an1}"LOOK IN THE TUNK."

11:48.370 --> 11:49.840
{\an1}HE MUST MEAN TRUNK.

11:52.470 --> 11:55.180
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hTICKETS TO
THE KRUSTY ANNIVERSARY SHOW!

11:55.240 --> 11:58.450
{\an1}OH, HE MUST WANT ME
\h\h\h\hTO GO WITH HIM.

11:58.510 --> 11:59.680
{\an1}IT ISN'T FAIR.

11:59.750 --> 12:02.480
{\an1}I'M TEN TIMES
THE KRUSTY FAN YOU ARE.

12:02.550 --> 12:05.820
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hI EVEN HAVE
THE KRUSTY HOME PREGNANCY TEST.

12:05.890 --> 12:07.250
{\an1}I'M NOT SURE I SHOULD GO.

12:07.320 --> 12:08.620
{\an1}I DON'T EVEN LIKE HIM.

12:08.690 --> 12:10.120
{\an1}YOU'RE RIGHT, LIS.
YOU SHOULDN'T GO.

12:10.190 --> 12:11.390
{\an1}IT WOULDN'T BE HONEST.

12:11.460 --> 12:13.430
{\an1}I'LL GO, DISGUISED AS YOU.

12:13.490 --> 12:15.400
{\an1}WHAT IF HE WANTS TO HOLD HANDS?

12:15.460 --> 12:17.100
{\an1}I'M PREPARED TO MAKE
THAT SACRIFICE.

12:17.170 --> 12:18.580
{\an1}WHAT IF HE WANTS A KISS?

12:18.630 --> 12:19.930
{\an1}I'M PREPARED TO MAKE
THAT SACRIFICE.

12:20.000 --> 12:21.140
{\an1}WHAT IF--

12:21.200 --> 12:22.440
{\an1}YOU DON'T WANT TO KNOW
HOW FAR I'LL GO.

12:22.500 --> 12:24.170
{\an1}DAD, IS IT RIGHT

12:24.240 --> 12:27.370
{\an1}TO TAKE THINGS FROM PEOPLE
\h\h\h\h\h\hYOU DON'T LIKE?

12:27.440 --> 12:28.980
{\an1}SURE IT IS, HONEY.

12:29.040 --> 12:31.110
{\an1}YOU DO MEAN STEALING, DON'T YOU?

12:31.180 --> 12:33.710
{\an1}IT'S NOT AS BAD
\h\hAS STEALING

12:33.780 --> 12:35.450
{\an1}BUT MY CONSCIENCE
IS BOTHERING ME.

12:35.520 --> 12:36.780
{\an1}YOUR CONSCIENCE?

12:36.850 --> 12:39.390
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\hLISA, DON'T LET
THAT PUSHY, LITTLE WEENIE

12:39.450 --> 12:41.420
{\an1}TELL YOU WHAT TO DO.

12:41.490 --> 12:44.060
{\an1}HOMER, THAT'S
A TERRIBLE THING TO SAY.

12:44.130 --> 12:45.190
{\an1}OH, SHUT UP.

12:45.260 --> 12:46.330
{\an1}YES, SIR.

12:48.160 --> 12:51.670
{\an1}\h\h\hI AM SO GLAD YOU
CHO-CHO-CHOOSE TO COME.

12:51.730 --> 12:54.840
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\h\hI THINK YOU SHOULD
GIVE THAT A REST, RALPH.

12:54.900 --> 12:57.000
{\an1}HOW DID YOU GET
THESE TICKETS?

12:57.070 --> 12:58.910
{\an1}\h\hKRUSTY KNOWS
HOW TO PLAY BALL.

13:03.280 --> 13:06.280
{\an1}AH... NOTHING BEATS
A GOOD PORNO MOVIE.

13:06.350 --> 13:07.310
{\an1}CHIEF WIGGUM

13:07.380 --> 13:08.920
{\an1}IS THIS A BUST?

13:08.980 --> 13:10.120
{\an1}UH, YEAH.

13:10.180 --> 13:12.690
{\an1}THAT'S JUST WHAT IT IS--
A BUST.

13:12.750 --> 13:14.760
{\an1}THAT STORY ISN'T SUITABLE
\h\h\h\h\h\hFOR CHILDREN.

13:14.820 --> 13:17.290
{\an1}REALLY? I KEEP MY PANTS ON
\h\h\h\h\hIN THIS VERSION.

13:19.260 --> 13:22.560
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\h\h\hAnnouncer:
It's the Krusty the Clown
\h29th Anniversary Show!

13:22.630 --> 13:24.000
{\an1}HEY!

13:24.070 --> 13:26.710
{\an1}( <i>applause and cheering )</i>

13:26.770 --> 13:28.200
{\an1}THANK YOU. THANK YOU.

13:28.270 --> 13:30.370
{\an1}HEY, MR. PRESIDENT.

13:30.440 --> 13:31.710
{\an1}\h\hI CAMPAIGNED
FOR THE OTHER GUY

13:31.770 --> 13:33.440
{\an1}BUT I VOTED FOR YOU.

13:33.510 --> 13:34.810
{\an1}( <i>goofy laughter )</i>

13:34.880 --> 13:38.350
{\an1}YOU KNOW, I STARTED THIS SHOW
\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hSO LONG AGO

13:38.410 --> 13:42.080
{\an1}THE AYATOLLAH ONLY HAD A GOATEE.

13:45.650 --> 13:46.820
{\an1}WHAT'S THE MATTER--

13:46.890 --> 13:48.860
{\an1}DON'T YOU PEOPLE
READ THE PAPERS?

13:48.920 --> 13:50.990
{\an1}AH, LET'S LOOK AT SOME CLIPS.

13:52.360 --> 13:55.160
{\an1}"He will not see me
\h\h\hstopping here

13:55.230 --> 13:57.830
{\an1}\hto watch his woods
fill up with snow..."

13:57.900 --> 14:02.070
{\an1}\h\hHey, Frosty, you
want some snow, man?

14:02.140 --> 14:05.710
{\an1}We discussed this,
\h\hand I said no.

14:05.770 --> 14:07.980
{\an1}( <i>applause )</i>

14:08.040 --> 14:10.380
{\an1}NOW, HERE'S A CLIP FROM 1973.

14:10.450 --> 14:13.920
{\an1}♪ Try to run, try to hide ♪

14:13.980 --> 14:16.680
{\an1}♪ Break on through
to the other side ♪

14:16.750 --> 14:19.750
{\an1}♪ Yeah. ♪

14:19.820 --> 14:21.090
{\an1}Ah!

14:21.160 --> 14:22.490
{\an1}WHAT WAS I ON?

14:22.560 --> 14:25.730
{\an1}LISA, DO YOU WANT
A BITE OF MY ICE CREAM?

14:25.790 --> 14:27.030
{\an1}NO, THANKS.

14:27.100 --> 14:29.010
{\an1}SEND IT THIS WAY, BOY.

14:29.060 --> 14:30.460
{\an1}WHOOPS.

14:30.530 --> 14:33.000
{\an1}\h\h\hAW... NOTHING
GETS CHOCOLATE OUT.

14:33.070 --> 14:34.340
{\an1}SEE?

14:34.400 --> 14:37.100
{\an1}I'VE WORKED WITH SOME MARVELOUS
\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hSECOND BANANAS

14:37.170 --> 14:38.470
{\an1}OVER THE YEARS

14:38.540 --> 14:41.180
{\an1}BUT NONE MORE MEMORABLE
\hTHAN SIDESHOW RAHEEM.

14:41.240 --> 14:45.510
{\an1}Uh, the script says I'm supposed
\h\h\h\hto bonk you with this.

14:45.580 --> 14:46.880
{\an1}I wouldn't.

14:46.950 --> 14:48.280
{\an1}Right on.

14:48.350 --> 14:51.190
{\an1}( <i>queasy groan )</i>

14:51.250 --> 14:53.490
{\an1}( <i>applause )</i>

14:53.550 --> 14:56.160
{\an1}ANGRY, ANGRY YOUNG MAN.

14:56.220 --> 14:59.060
{\an1}NOW FOR MY FAVORITE PART
\h\h\h\h\h\hOF THE SHOW.

14:59.130 --> 15:01.030
{\an1}WHAT'S THAT SAY?

15:01.100 --> 15:03.030
{\an1}"TALK TO THE AUDIENCE"?

15:03.100 --> 15:05.300
{\an1}OH, GOD, THIS IS ALWAYS DEATH.

15:05.370 --> 15:06.670
{\an1}ALL RIGHT.

15:06.730 --> 15:08.970
{\an1}OH, NO, PLEASE DON'T
\hSHOW ME WITH RALPH.

15:09.040 --> 15:10.700
{\an1}WHAT'S YOUR NAME, SON?

15:10.770 --> 15:12.140
{\an1}RALPH.

15:12.210 --> 15:13.470
{\an1}( <i>whimpers )</i>

15:13.540 --> 15:15.740
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\h\hAND IS THIS
YOUR GIRLFRIEND, RALPH?

15:15.810 --> 15:17.810
{\an1}YES, I LOVE LISA SIMPSON

15:17.880 --> 15:20.710
{\an1}\h\hAND WHEN I GROW UP,
I'M GOING TO MARRY HER.

15:20.780 --> 15:22.420
{\an1}NO!

15:22.480 --> 15:23.750
{\an1}NOW YOU LISTEN TO ME.

15:23.820 --> 15:25.090
{\an1}I DON'T LIKE YOU.

15:25.150 --> 15:26.490
{\an1}I NEVER LIKED YOU.

15:26.550 --> 15:28.690
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hTHE ONLY REASON
I GAVE YOU THAT VALENTINE

15:28.760 --> 15:30.220
{\an1}\h\h\h\hwas because
nobody else would!

15:30.290 --> 15:32.130
{\an1}WATCH THIS, LISE.

15:32.190 --> 15:35.260
{\an1}YOU CAN ACTUALLY PINPOINT
\h\h\hTHE SECOND WHEN HIS
\h\h\hHEART RIPS IN HALF.

15:35.330 --> 15:38.270
{\an1}AND... NOW.

15:40.070 --> 15:41.600
{\an1}( <i>groans )</i>

15:47.440 --> 15:50.140
{\an1}AT LEAST YOU GUYS
\hARE MY FRIENDS.

15:52.750 --> 15:54.850
{\an1}( <i>sighing )</i>

15:54.920 --> 15:56.820
{\an1}SON, I KNOW JUST
\h\hHOW YOU FEEL.

15:56.880 --> 15:59.690
{\an1}YOU'VE GOT A GREAT LITTLE GIRL
\hAND THE WORLD'S YOUR OYSTER.

15:59.750 --> 16:02.120
{\an1}NO, DAD, SHE MADE
A FOOL OUT OF ME.

16:02.190 --> 16:04.860
{\an1}HEY, COME TO THINK OF IT,
\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hSHE DID.

16:04.930 --> 16:07.900
{\an1}WELL, SHE DIDN'T RECKON

16:07.960 --> 16:10.830
{\an1}WITH THE AWESOME POWER
OF THE CHIEF OF POLICE.

16:10.900 --> 16:13.030
{\an1}NOW, WHERE DID I PUT MY BADGE?

16:13.100 --> 16:14.370
{\an1}HEY!

16:14.440 --> 16:16.470
{\an1}THAT DUCK'S GOT IT.

16:16.540 --> 16:18.710
{\an1}COME ON, COME ON,
\h\hGIVE IT BACK.

16:18.770 --> 16:20.040
{\an1}I NEED IT.

16:20.110 --> 16:21.240
{\an1}AH, KEEP IT.

16:23.240 --> 16:25.310
{\an1}( <i>police siren warbling )</i>

16:25.380 --> 16:27.250
{\an1}SOMETHING WRONG, OFFICER?

16:27.320 --> 16:29.660
{\an1}YEAH, GOT A TAILLIGHT OUT.

16:29.720 --> 16:31.450
{\an1}WHERE?

16:31.520 --> 16:32.950
{\an1}RIGHT THERE.

16:33.020 --> 16:35.890
{\an1}ONE DAY HONEST CITIZENS
\hARE GOING TO STAND UP

16:35.960 --> 16:37.590
{\an1}TO YOU CROOKED COPS.

16:37.660 --> 16:39.290
{\an1}THEY ARE? OH, NO.

16:39.360 --> 16:40.960
{\an1}HAVE THEY SET A DATE?

16:47.570 --> 16:49.800
{\an1}\hTHIS ORANGE
\h\h\h\hDRINK IS
THE ONLY WAY

16:49.870 --> 16:52.410
{\an1}TO RECOUP OUR TERRIBLE LOSSES
\h\h\hFROM "FIRE DRILL FOLLIES."

16:52.470 --> 16:54.680
{\an1}I JUST DON'T KNOW
WHAT WENT WRONG.

16:54.740 --> 16:57.280
{\an1}YOU OPENED THE SHOW
WITH A FIRE DRILL

16:57.350 --> 16:58.990
{\an1}AND EVERYONE CLEARED OUT.

16:59.050 --> 17:00.880
{\an1}SO MOTHER WAS RIGHT.

17:00.950 --> 17:02.320
{\an1}IT WAS MY FAULT.

17:02.380 --> 17:04.990
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hGO AHEAD,
WATER IT DOWN SOME MORE.

17:05.050 --> 17:08.859
{\an1}MY GOD, MAN, I'VE WATERED HER
\h\hDOWN AS FAR AS SHE'LL GO.

17:08.920 --> 17:10.819
{\an1}I CANNOT WATER NO MORE.

17:12.089 --> 17:13.589
{\an1}GOOD EVENING, EVERYONE,
\h\h\h\h\h\hAND WELCOME

17:13.660 --> 17:15.560
{\an1}TO A WONDERFUL EVENING
\h\h\h\h\h\hOF THEATER

17:15.630 --> 17:17.770
{\an1}AND PICKING UP AFTER YOURSELVES.

17:19.569 --> 17:23.400
{\an1}\h\h\h\hWE BEGIN WITH A TRIBUTE
TO OUR LESSER-KNOWN PRESIDENTS.

17:23.470 --> 17:26.569
{\an1}( <i>"Hail to the Chief" playing)</i>

17:26.640 --> 17:29.610
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h♪ WE ARE
THE MEDIOCRE PRESIDENTS ♪

17:29.680 --> 17:33.980
{\an1}♪ YOU WON'T FIND OUR FACES
\hON DOLLARS OR ON CENTS ♪

17:34.050 --> 17:35.950
{\an1}♪ THERE'S TAYLOR,
\hTHERE'S TYLER ♪

17:36.020 --> 17:37.620
{\an1}♪ THERE'S FILLMORE
AND THERE'S HAYES ♪

17:37.690 --> 17:39.000
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h♪ THERE'S
WILLIAM HENRY HARRISON ♪

17:39.050 --> 17:40.720
{\an1}♪ I DIED IN 30 DAYS ♪

17:40.790 --> 17:45.990
{\an1}♪ WE ARE THE ADEQUATE,
\h\h\h\h\hFORGETTABLE ♪

17:46.060 --> 17:48.830
{\an1}♪ OCCASIONALLY REGRETTABLE ♪

17:48.900 --> 17:51.570
{\an1}♪ CARETAKER PRESIDENTS ♪

17:51.630 --> 17:55.840
{\an1}♪ OF THE U.S.A. ♪

18:02.740 --> 18:05.310
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hHEY GIRLS,
CHECK OUT THIS PRESIDENT.

18:05.380 --> 18:07.480
{\an1}( <i>imitating Nixon: )
\h\hI AM NOT A BUTT.</i>

18:07.550 --> 18:09.680
{\an1}( <i>screaming )</i>

18:09.750 --> 18:11.420
{\an1}BART, DO YOU WANT TO PLAY
\h\h\h\hJOHN WILKES BOOTH

18:11.490 --> 18:13.190
{\an1}OR ACT LIKE A MANIAC?

18:13.250 --> 18:13.920
{\an1}I'LL BE GOOD.

18:17.190 --> 18:19.960
{\an1}RALPH, I'M SORRY I...

18:20.030 --> 18:21.130
{\an1}LEAVE ME ALONE.

18:21.200 --> 18:23.500
{\an1}\hI'M HERE TO PLAY
GEORGE WASHINGTON.

18:23.560 --> 18:26.730
{\an1}UH... RALPH?

18:26.800 --> 18:30.840
{\an1}MISS HOOVER, THIS BEARD'S
\h\h\h\hGIVING ME A RASH.

18:30.910 --> 18:32.980
{\an1}MILHOUSE, YOU HAVE ONE LINE
\h\h\hAND THEN YOU'RE SHOT.

18:33.040 --> 18:34.580
{\an1}NOW GET OUT THERE.

18:35.880 --> 18:39.210
{\an1}I THOUGHT THAT CIVIL WAR
\h\h\h\hWOULD NEVER END.

18:39.280 --> 18:41.080
{\an1}NOW TO SOOTHE MY HEAD

18:41.150 --> 18:44.050
{\an1}\h\hWITH AN EVENING
AT FORD'S THEATER.

18:44.120 --> 18:46.920
{\an1}OH, NO, JOHN WILKES BOOTH!

18:46.990 --> 18:49.090
{\an1}<i>HASTA LA VISTA, ABIE.</i>

18:52.790 --> 18:54.660
{\an1}COME ON BOY, FINISH HIM OFF.

18:56.160 --> 18:58.600
{\an1}YOU'RE NEXT, CHESTER A. ARTHUR.

19:01.170 --> 19:02.700
{\an1}UNHAND ME, YANKEE.

19:02.770 --> 19:05.170
{\an1}AND NOW OUR EVENING
\hCOMES TO AN END.

19:05.240 --> 19:06.010
{\an1}WOO-HOO!

19:06.070 --> 19:07.740
{\an1}WITH A THOROUGH RE-TELLING

19:07.810 --> 19:09.680
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\hOF THE LIFE
OF GEORGE WASHINGTON.

19:09.740 --> 19:10.780
{\an1}Homer:
D-OHH!

19:14.180 --> 19:16.780
{\an1}DEAR, DEAR GEORGE WASHINGTON.

19:16.850 --> 19:20.220
{\an1}CAN THIS LIBERTY YOU DREAM OF
BE WORTH ALL THIS BLOODSHED?

19:22.520 --> 19:23.960
{\an1}WELL, CAN IT?

19:28.260 --> 19:31.100
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hDEAR MADAM,
WOULD YOU PUT A PRICE

19:31.170 --> 19:33.200
{\an1}ON THE AIR WE BREATHE

19:33.270 --> 19:35.800
{\an1}OR THE PROVIDENCE
THAT SUSTAINS US?

19:35.870 --> 19:38.370
{\an1}\h\h\hCOULDN'T WE JUST
GIVE IN TO THE BRITISH?

19:38.440 --> 19:39.940
{\an1}NEVER!

19:41.910 --> 19:45.150
{\an1}THAT BOY IS MAGNIFICENT.

19:45.210 --> 19:48.420
{\an1}HE MAKES ME WANT TO LEARN MORE
\h\hABOUT OUR FOUNDING FATHERS.

19:48.480 --> 19:50.020
{\an1}TO THE LIBRARY.

19:50.080 --> 19:51.450
{\an1}YEAH!

19:51.520 --> 19:55.020
{\an1}DEAR MARTHA, I FEAR
MY TIME IS AT HAND.

19:55.090 --> 19:58.190
{\an1}OH, GEORGE.

19:58.260 --> 20:00.430
{\an1}\h\hYOUR BROTH,
MR. PRESIDENT.

20:00.490 --> 20:02.500
{\an1}I ASKED FOR NO BROTH.

20:02.560 --> 20:06.230
{\an1}AWAY WITH YOU, LEST MY CANE
\h\h\h\hFIND YOUR BACKSIDE.

20:06.300 --> 20:07.700
{\an1}YES.

20:07.770 --> 20:10.740
{\an1}( <i>sobbing )</i>

20:10.810 --> 20:13.080
{\an1}PLEASE DON'T LEAVE ME,
\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hGEORGE.

20:13.140 --> 20:16.480
{\an1}DEAR WIFE, IF I COULD TAKE
\h\h\h\h\hBUT ONE TREASURE

20:16.540 --> 20:18.950
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hWITH ME
TO THE NEXT LIFE

20:19.010 --> 20:21.350
{\an1}\h\h\hIT WOULD BE
YOUR TENDER KISS.

20:23.120 --> 20:25.050
{\an1}MMM...

20:25.120 --> 20:27.320
{\an1}NOW THAT'S A MAN.

20:34.200 --> 20:35.640
{\an1}I DID NOT CRY

20:35.700 --> 20:38.730
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hWHEN ME OWN FATHER
WAS HUNG FOR STEALING A PIG

20:38.800 --> 20:41.100
{\an1}BUT I'LL CRY NOW.

20:41.170 --> 20:42.970
{\an1}( <i>sobbing )</i>

20:48.210 --> 20:55.250
{\an1}♪ ...From sea to shining sea. ♪

20:55.320 --> 20:56.550
{\an1}Thanks for coming.

20:56.620 --> 20:57.550
{\an1}DON'T FORGET

20:57.620 --> 21:00.190
{\an1}to purchase some orange drink

21:00.250 --> 21:02.190
{\an1}for the long ride home.

21:02.260 --> 21:03.520
{\an1}RALPH!

21:03.590 --> 21:04.960
{\an1}RALPH!

21:05.030 --> 21:06.930
{\an1}RALPH!

21:06.990 --> 21:08.330
{\an1}LISA.

21:08.400 --> 21:09.630
{\an1}HI, RALPH.

21:09.700 --> 21:11.370
{\an1}YOU WERE GREAT TONIGHT.

21:11.430 --> 21:12.930
{\an1}AW, THANKS.

21:13.000 --> 21:14.840
{\an1}I'VE GOT SOMETHING
\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hFOR YOU.

21:14.900 --> 21:17.740
{\an1}"LET'S BEE FRIENDS!"

21:17.810 --> 21:19.020
{\an1}IT SAYS "BEE"

21:19.070 --> 21:21.980
{\an1}AND THERE'S A PICTURE
OF A BEE ON IT.

21:22.040 --> 21:24.510
{\an1}I THOUGHT YOU'D LIKE IT.

21:26.150 --> 21:28.980
{\an1}OH, LOOK AT THAT.

21:29.050 --> 21:30.280
{\an1}Attention, all units.

21:30.350 --> 21:31.820
{\an1}Riot in progress at...

21:31.890 --> 21:33.720
{\an1}NOT TONIGHT.

21:33.790 --> 21:35.660
{\an1}...Bill and Marty here
\h\h\h\h\h\hwrapping up

21:35.720 --> 21:37.090
{\an1}a beautiful President's Day.

21:37.160 --> 21:39.130
{\an1}To George and Abe
and all the rest

21:39.190 --> 21:41.630
{\an1}here's a special song
\h\h\h\hjust for you.

21:41.700 --> 21:44.700
{\an1}♪ I was working in the lab
\h\h\h\h\hlate one night ♪

21:44.770 --> 21:46.500
{\an1}Doggone it!

21:46.570 --> 21:48.940
{\an1}♪ When my eyes beheld
\h\han eerie sight ♪

21:49.000 --> 21:52.210
{\an1}♪ For my monster from his slab
\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hbegan to rise ♪

21:52.270 --> 21:55.080
{\an1}♪ and suddenly to my surprise ♪

21:55.140 --> 21:56.640
{\an1}♪ <i>He did the mash ♪</i>

21:56.710 --> 21:58.380
{\an1}♪ He did the monster mash ♪

21:58.450 --> 21:59.710
{\an1}♪ <i>The monster mash ♪</i>

21:59.780 --> 22:01.780
{\an1}♪ It was a graveyard smash ♪

22:01.850 --> 22:03.520
{\an1}♪ <i>He did the mash ♪</i>

22:03.580 --> 22:05.390
{\an1}♪ It caught on in a flash ♪

22:05.450 --> 22:06.990
{\an1}♪ <i>He did the mash ♪</i>

22:07.050 --> 22:09.420
{\an1}♪ He did the monster mash ♪

22:09.490 --> 22:11.930
{\an1}♪ From my laboratory
in the castle east ♪

22:11.990 --> 22:15.760
{\an1}\h\h♪ To the master bedroom
where the vampires feast ♪

22:15.830 --> 22:19.570
{\an1}\h\h\h♪ The ghouls all came
from their humble abodes ♪

22:19.630 --> 22:22.070
{\an1}\h\h♪ To catch a jolt
from my electrodes ♪

22:22.140 --> 22:23.270
{\an1}♪ <i>They did the mash... ♪</i>

22:23.340 --> 22:25.840
{\an1}♪ <i>They did the monster mash. ♪</i>

22:25.910 --> 22:26.970
{\an1}♪ <i>The monster mash ♪</i>

22:27.040 --> 22:28.880
{\an1}♪ It was a graveyard smash... ♪

22:28.940 --> 22:30.380
{\an1}♪ They did the mash. ♪

22:30.440 --> 22:32.210
{\an1}♪ It caught on in a flash. ♪

22:32.280 --> 22:34.010
